---
title: Greek Pearl Pasta Salad with Feta & Dill plus Tomatoes, Green Olives & Cucumber
description: This light, bright lunch delivers all the bright freshness of a Greek salad—lemon, olives, feta, cucumbers, and tomatoes—plus the herbaceousness of dill. For our spin, we toss in springy pearl couscous to keep you going all afternoon. And the ultimate selling point: It takes just a quick 15 minutes to make!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/663a6cfdfe8a253ad9a7a9bc-d33b3f0a.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/663a6cfdfe8a253ad9a7a9bc-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 14 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 860 mg
cuisine: Southern Europe
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/greek-pearl-pasta-salad-with-feta-and-dill-663a6cfdfe8a253ad9a7a9bc
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli Couscous{5%ounce} and 11⁄2 cups water (3 cups
for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until
tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain, then rinse with cold water until cooled. Shake
off excess water.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise.
Halve @Mini Cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into 1⁄4-inch-thick half-moons. Drain
and halve @Green Olives{1}. Quarter @Lemon{1}. Roughly chop @Dill{1/4%ounce}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @Greek Vinaigrette{1.5%ounce}, tomatoes, cucumber,
olives, @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, and as much dill
as you like (2 TBSP olive oil and juice from two lemon wedges for 4 servings).

Add couscous to bowl with veggies. Add @Feta Cheese{1/2%cup} and a squeeze of
lemon juice to taste; toss to combine. Taste and season with @Salt{} and
@Pepper{}.

Divide salad between bowls and serve.